                  <provenance> A signature on both sides (upside down and very faded on the recto) <q type="inscription"><persName key="person_2545" role="sgn">Wyllyam Brereton</persName></q>; also on the verso <q type="inscription"><persName key="person_2543" role="sgn">Iame tayler</persName></q> and <q type="inscription"><persName key="person_2541" role="sgn">Anne Bere</persName></q>. The first may be one of the several Cheshire men of the name active in the early sixteenth century, e.g. Sir William of Brereton Green, who died as Lord Justice of Ireland in 1541.</provenance>
